description_clean:
At Flix, we offer a dynamic work environment with competitive pay, strong growth opportunities, and a tech-driven approach to making travel more accessible, sustainable, and affordable. &nbsp;
We're&nbsp;looking for a motivated and skilled&nbsp;Senior Data Platform Engineer&nbsp;to join our&nbsp;Core Data Platform team&nbsp;– Foundation Division. You will help us drive the company to the next&nbsp;level, and&nbsp;have the most direct influence on our success.&nbsp;
The team provides tools, infrastructure,&nbsp;expertise&nbsp;and best practices to empower every Flix employee through data excellence and reliable infrastructure. We put our users into the heart of our data platform, ensuring that they can easily process, discover, analyze,&nbsp;share&nbsp;and&nbsp;leverage&nbsp;data. We have a constant process of reflecting on our current&nbsp;work, and&nbsp;adapting new practices and technologies. Our daily work is built on trust and collaboration.&nbsp;
About the Role

Improve and&nbsp;maintain&nbsp;our scalable data platform infrastructure on AWS, K8s, Confluent Cloud and Snowflake, ensuring high availability and reliability for all data consumers across the organization
Collaborate closely with data engineers, analysts, and product teams to understand their needs and continuously improve the platform's usability and self-service capabilities
Develop and maintain infrastructure-as-code using Terraform, ensuring our cloud environments are reproducible, auditable, and well-documented
Operate and improve our data platform by optimizing workloads for performance, cost-efficiency, and resilience
Build and refine CI/CD pipelines (GitLab) to enable fast, safe, and automated deployments across the data platform
Evaluate and introduce new technologies and best practices to keep our data platform modern, secure, and future-proof
Contribute to architectural decisions and technical documentation, sharing knowledge within the team and across the organization
Implement and maintain comprehensive observability and monitoring (Datadog), creating actionable alerts and dashboards to proactively detect and resolve issues
Participate in the team's on-call duty schedule&nbsp;

About You

Strong data architecture experience, with a proven track record of solving complex data challenges in large or multi-team organizations
The right cultural fit: a genuine desire to help colleagues, a focus on delivering the&nbsp;right solution over the fast one, and comfort with frequent context switching
Strong Kafka knowledge from architecture and a developer's perspective, enabling hands-on support for application developers and contributing to our infrastructure
Extensive experience with scalable data platforms in complex environments, including ownership of platform-critical applications
End-to-end infrastructure ownership —&nbsp; CI/CD (GitLab), observability &amp; monitoring (Datadog) — with the ability to create meaningful, actionable monitors
Solid Terraform knowledge to confidently navigate,&nbsp;maintain, and contribute to our infrastructure-as-code codebase
On-call experience and a clear mindset that critical issues&nbsp;don't&nbsp;follow business hours
Solid experience with a Cloud Provider (preferably AWS)
Hands-on experience with Kubernetes
Fluent in English, with strong technical communication skills adaptable to diverse audiences.&nbsp;

Nice-to-have:

Experience with&nbsp;Snowflake or comparable cloud data warehouse solutions (e.g., Databricks,&nbsp;BigQuery, Redshift)
Network/Security knowledge (e.g.&nbsp;SSO, SAML, VPCs, network policies,&nbsp;EntraID)
Previous experience working in a&nbsp;central or shared data platform team
Exposure to or interest in AI/ML workloads on data platforms

We recognize that everyone carries a unique set of valuable skills and experiences. If you think you could have an impact even though you don't meet 100% of the requirements, we still encourage you to apply. We want to hear from you! &nbsp;
What We Offer

Travel perks: 12 free Flix vouchers + 12 discount vouchers for friends &amp; family.&nbsp;
Work from (M)Anywhere: Depending on your role, work from another location for up to 60 days per year.&nbsp;
Hybrid work model: We are an office-first company, but we offer flexibility to balance work and life.&nbsp;
Wellbeing support: Access confidential 1:1 counselling, courses, and stress management for yourself and up to four family members.&nbsp;
Learning &amp; Development: Take advantage of language classes, training courses, and expert-led sessions to grow your skills.&nbsp;
Mentoring Program: Connect with experienced colleagues to gain insights and accelerate your career.&nbsp;

To view more local benefits specific to each office location, please check out this link:&nbsp;Locations - Flix Career

Why Join Flix?
At Flix, you'll find teams that rally together to overcome challenges and spark creativity. We believe in ownership culture - giving you the freedom to take initiative, make an impact, and shape your own career path.As we continue to expand across the globe, you can make a real difference in how we work.
If you're ready to grow and lead your journey, Flix is the place for you!&nbsp;

